HEADWORD: Double-minded
<hw>Dou"ble-mind"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
different minds at different times; unsettled; undetermined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>double-minded</qex> man is unstable in all his ways.</q>
<rj><qau>Jas. i. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doubleness</ent>⟦br⟧
